                                <br />
                                <br />
                                <p>The Wyrd of Stromgard is an expansion for Dungeon World (who in turn is Powered by the Apocalypse).  It is a sleek, modern ruleset that lets the collaborative narrative of roleplaying lead the way while the mechanics cleverly quantify contest points in an easy to read and easy to learn fashion that frankly opens up tabletop RPGs to a huge variety of people.</p>
                                <p>The Dungeon World ruleset is the perfect vehicle for Stromgard.  The rules place priority on role playing and story telling, while still providing a fun and interesting combat system without bogging itself down in a multitude of complex, rarely used rules.  It's easy to pick up, easy to get good at, and robust enough to handly really complex, nuanced situations in very common sense ways.</p>
                                <p>For those of you familiar with Dungeon World, you're probably thinking of the GM Principles right now.  I know the goal is to "draw maps, but leave blanks" and The Wyrd of Stromgard offers the perfect balance of structure and customizabilty to make the GM's job a little easier and simultaneously provide a fantastic, dynamic setting that play groups can alter and customize any way they please.</p>
                                <p>Of course, this sounds like a perfect match, you think.  Well, now you'll need to grab the Dungeon World core rules and get yourself aquainted!  Check out <a href="http://www.dungeon-world.com/">Dungeon World's</a> website for all the info you could possibly need.  Even better, Wyrd of Stromgard player classes can play side by side with vanilla Dungeon World characters seamlessly.</p>
