                                <h3>The Bearskin</h3>
                                <p>The Bearskin is a physical powerhouse.  In the heat of battle they succumb to their bloodrage, transforming them from mortal warrior to a nearly-impervious force of sheer destruction.  They have nerves of steel, an indomitable will to triumph, and can single handedly turn an enemy onslaught into a one-sided bloodbath.  The Bearskin cannot keep up their frenzy forever, on the other hand, and they crash hard, leaving them vulnerable.  A Bearskin's allies also learn quickly to give them room during a fight, less they wind up amongst the body count.</p>
                                <h3>The Skald</h3>
                                <p>The Skald is a lorekeeper and academic, a highly valued member of society by all classes and creeds.  Jarls depend on them to record their lineage, heroes want them to sing of their deeds...  People believe that Skalds hold great magic in their words, and they are often consulted as mediators and trustworthy enough to have the final say in many grave matters.  Skalds will find it easy to leverage their social status in most situations, from deescalating combat or intentionally inflaming it.  Skalds are also talented fighters in their own right and can hold their own in a hairy situation.</p>
                                <h3>The Hunter</h3>
                                <p>Hailing from a mysterious, shadowy cult, Hunters are devoted to a ghastly phenomenon called The Wild Hunt.  This mysterious occurence consists of a ravenous, demonic hunting party rampaging across the land, dragging unpunished criminals, murderers, oathbreakers and other unworthy out of their hiding places to be dragged off to Helheim, jail of the dishonorable dead.  The Hunter is a vigilante, skilled at stalking in the shadows but a hard hitting, sadistic fighter bent on debilitating their enemy.  They're ruthless and sometimes quite bloodthirsty but don't expect to take one into a fight where you intend to let your enemies live.</p>
